{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐνδια-τρίβω</b> [ῑ], <br /> <i>perfect</i> <b>-τέτρῐφα</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 357a4 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>spend</b> or <b>consume in</b> doing, Χρόνον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 714, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.18, 85. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>absolutely</i> (i.e. Χρόνον or βίον), <b>spend time in</b> a place, αὐτόθι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 33.5; τῇ Χώρᾳ 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.88.1, etc.; ἐν τόπῳ 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 5.44 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἀνθρωπίσκοις <b>among</b> them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Alex.” 33. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>waste time by staying in</b> a place, <b>linger</b> there, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.12, 7.81, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>continue in</b> the practice of a thing, τοῖς ἠθάσι.. τοῖς ἀρχαίοις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 585, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 484c, “R.” 487d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐᾶν ἐνδιατρίβειν τὴν ὄψιν ἔν τινι let one's eyes <b>linger on</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.1.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. λόγοις καὶ ἔργοις <b>linger fondly on</b> them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nigr.” 7; τῇ περὶ τοὺς βίους ἀναγραφῇ 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pericles” 2; κατὰ φιλοσοφίαν 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 217; περὶ μουσικήν 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 14.623e; ἐ. ὅθεν ἡσυχιεῖ 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “De rerum natura - Wien. Stud.” 27 G.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; especially <b>dwell upon a point</b> (in speaking), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.201, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1258b35, 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 1.45b; περί τινος 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 989b27; τῷ Χρησίμῳ 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “προγυμνάσματα” 7, etc. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7224","accentedUnicode":"ἐνδιατρίβω","shortDef":"to spend one's time","mediumDef":"to spend one's time","stepGloss":"to spend one's time","stepTransliteration":"endiatribō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}